               <head>Jamiʻ-i ʻAbbasi</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Jāmiʻ-i ʻAbbāsī by ʻĀmilī, Bahāʾ al-Dīn Muḥammad ibn Ḥusayn, 1547-1621</summary>
                  <msItem n="1" class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008104962" xml:id="Uk_Or_15922-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656953.0x000001 viaf_27052262">ʻĀmilī, Bahāʾ al-Dīn Muḥammad ibn Ḥusayn, 1547-1621</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656953.0x000001 viaf_27052262" type="supplied">العاملي، بهاء الدين محمد بن حسين
</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_1167">Jāmiʻ-i ʻAbbāsī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_1167">
جامع عباسي</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>A general treatise on Shī‘a jurisprudence. By Bahā’ al-Dīn ‘Āmilī (d. 1030/1621).
</p>
                        <p>
For references to this author see E. Kohlberg, ‘Bahā’-al-Dīn ‘Āmelī, Shaikh Moḥammad b. Hosayn Bahā’ī’, EIr III, p. 429-30.
Other BL copies: Add. 23578 (Rieu I pp. 25-6).</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian with some Arabic</textLang>
                     <filiation/>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc form="codex">
                     <supportDesc material="chart">
                        <support>Thin beige paper; light worm damage in the margins, and light moisture staining throughout.</support>
