                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout columns="1" writtenLines="15">
                           <p>15 lines per page. </p>
                        </layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     <summary>Neat <term xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">naskhī</term>;  Arabic texts being vocalised. The copyist’s name is not entirely legible, but begins ‘Shaykh’ and includes two personal names, the second possibly being Yaḥyà.
                     </summary>
                     <handNote script="Arabic" scope="major"/>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                     <summary> Red headings and overlining. No text frames.</summary>
                     <decoNote/>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <p>A few notes in margins; front and end flyleaves, owners’ scribbles; f. 129v, inscription, mainly deleted, giving the name of the work and the number of folios as 130.  </p>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <p>Brown leather binding with blind-tooled border lines; spine with raised bands, in need of repair.</p>
                  </bindingDesc>
                  <sealDesc>
                     <summary> Seal impression of Aḥmad ibn Muḥammad Ḥusaynī (ff. 1r and 128v).</summary>
